  "text": "The Tl(I) (10 µg/L) reduction peak in the presence of Cu(II) (500 µg/L) was not altered with 1 M KNO 3 as electrolyte since the Cu-nitrate complex is very weak (Fig. 1c [B] ). The same was observed with sulfate ( Fig. 1c [C] ) (here the K 2 SO 4 concentration used was 3.3 × 10 -3 M at pH = 4 in order to simulate the sulfate concentration in a typical mining environment with acid mine drainage [CITATION_1] ).",
